Title: You're So Cupid

reviewText: This was a clean, cute movie about Cupid's daughters. The acting was cheesy, as was the storyline, everything was completely predictable, but i'm saying this as an adult. For ages, imo, 11-17, this movie would be a solid A, i'm sure. There are not many clean, fun movies like this around.
Title: You're So Cupid

reviewText: You're So Cupid is about twin girls named Emma and Lilly Valentine.  Emma (Danielle Chuchran) and Lilly(Caitlin E.J. Meyer) are high school seniors who has the desire to play matchmaker, even though they're have never been in love themselves.  But when the Valentine's dance is around the corner both Emma and Lilly fall in love with the new guy at their school, Connor (Jeremy Sumpter).  When the girls discover that they are falling for the same guy they do mean tricks on each other.  The girls put away their differences and try to put their separated parents, Daniel (Brain Krause) and Audrey (Lauren Holly) Valentine back to together.  Watch this movie to see each twin does Connor take to the dance.  Also Emma and Lilly figures out something about their dad. Find out what that something is? This movie is really cute! I hope everyone enjoys the movie as much as I do! Oh just a hint this movie is family approved.
Title: You're So Cupid

reviewText: This is a really cute family movie about sisters who are always helping people out with matters of the heart. Cute movie to watch with family around Valentines Day or anytime.
